{
  "abstract" : [
    {
      "text" : "SwiftPM 5.4 includes several improvements, all of which are opt-in based on specifying a tools version of 5.4.",
      "type" : "text"
    }
  ],
  "hierarchy" : {
    "paths" : [
      [
        "doc:\/\/PackageManagerDocs\/documentation\/PackageManagerDocs",
        "doc:\/\/PackageManagerDocs\/documentation\/PackageManagerDocs\/ReleaseNotes"
      ]
    ]
  },
  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/PackageManagerDocs\/documentation\/PackageManagerDocs\/5.4"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "modules" : [
      {
        "name" : "Swift Package Manager"
      }
    ],
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "SwiftPM 5.4 Release Notes"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Executable-targets",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Executable targets",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Swift packages that specify a 5.4 tools version can now explicitly declare targets as executable, which allows the use of the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "@main",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " keyword in package code.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This is done by declaring the target using ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "executableTarget()",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " in the package manifest, telling SwiftPM that the target should be considered to be executable regardless of whether it contains a file with a base name of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "main",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The compiler still applies its usual rules when compiling an executable module, so a single target cannot, for example, have a file named ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "main.swift",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and another file that uses ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "@main",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Automatic-test-discovery",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Automatic test discovery",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Automatic test discovery is now the default on all platforms, removing the need in ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "LinuxMain.swift",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", which has been deprecated. This file is still honored if it is present.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "More-flexible-tools-version-formatting",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "More flexible tools version formatting",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "code" : "Package",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " manifests can now have any combination of leading whitespace characters before the tools version comment. This allows more flexibility in formatting manifests.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Specifically, the Swift tools version specification in each manifest file now accepts any combination of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "horizontal",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " whitespace characters surrounding ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "swift-tools-version",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", if and only if the specified version ≥ ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "5.4",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". For example, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "\/\/swift-tools-version:\t5.4",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "\/\/\t\t swift-tools-version: 5.4",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " are valid.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "All ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/www.unicode.org\/reports\/tr14\/",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " are now recognised in ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Package",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " manifests. This ensures correctness in parsing manifests that are edited and\/or built on many non-Unix-like platforms that use ASCII or Unicode encodings.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Package-dependency-caching",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Package dependency caching",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Swift Package Manager now caches package dependency repositories on a per-user basis, which reduces the amount of network traffic and increases performance of dependency resolution for subsequent uses of the same package.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The default location of the cache differs depending on the platform, but can be controlled using the new ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--cache-path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " option. SwiftPM also creates a symbolic link at ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "~\/.swiftpm",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " referencing the default cache location.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Compiled package manifests are also now cached on a per-user basis. This can be overridden using the new ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--manifest-cache",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " option.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
